JOHANNESBURG - The Special Tribunal has ordered that controversial businessperson Hamilton Ndlovu be blacklisted from doing business with the state. On Tuesday, Ndlovu was ordered to pay back R158 million that he received through irregular PPE contracts. The multi-million rand tender worth R172 million was awarded by the National Health Laboratory Service to Ndlovu and his associated companies. The Special Investigating Unit said that it would now auction luxury properties worth R32 million linked to Ndlovu. CORRUPTION DOES NOT PAY @TribunalSpecial ordered that Hamilton Ndlovu be blacklisted.SIU to auction luxury properties worth R32M that are linked to Ndlovu.R10M in cash is forfeited to the state.OUTSTANDING: R116M pic.twitter.com/5bv5kIhJLL 